textBeforeTable: Related Commands task_id=70 service=exec port=10 protocol=telnet address=172.31.3.78 cmd=glare bytes_in=308 bytes_out=76 paks_in=45 paks_out=54 elapsed_time=14 16:49:47: AAA/ACCT: Connection acct stop: 16:49:32: AAA/ACCT: Connect start, line 10, glare 16:49:21: AAA/ACCT: EXEC acct start, line 10 Router# debug aaa accounting  The following is sample output from the debugaaaaccounting command: Examples     You can also use the showaccountingcommand to step through all active sessions and to print all the accounting records for actively accounted functions. The showaccounting command allows you to display the active "accountable events" on the system. It provides systems administrators a quick look at what is happening, and may also be useful for collecting information in the event of a data loss of some kind on the accounting server. The showaccounting command displays additional data on the internal state of the authentication, authorization, and accounting (AAA) security system if debugaaaaccounting is turned on as well. The information displayed by the debugaaaaccounting command is independent of the accounting protocol used to transfer the accounting information to a server. Use the debugtacacs and debugradius protocol-specific commands to get more detailed information about protocol-level issues. Usage Guidelines
